Ascites:

• Ascites is the accumulation of excess fluid in the abdominal area

Symptoms to look for:

• Swelling of the abdomen
• As condition worsens one experiences
   o Abdominal pain 
   o Discomfort
   o Bloating
• There is an increase in pressure on the diaphragm, causing shortness of breath

Causes:

• Cirrhosis of liver
• Increased pressure of liver blood flow 

Natural home remedy using bitter gourds:

1. Wash and remove the skin of 3-4 bitter gourds 
2. De-seed it and crush the bitter gourds
3. Place the paste on a sieve and extract the juice
4. Mix equal quantity of water 
5. Drink 3 times a day

Natural home remedy using fenugreek seeds: 

1. Soak 3 tbsp fenugreek seeds overnight in 1 cup of water
2. Strain the water in the morning
3. Drink on an empty stomach

Natural home remedy using chickpeas:

1. Soak 1 cup of chickpeas overnight in water 
2. Consume these the next day
3. Add salt and pepper to taste

